In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Karine Jean-Pierre addressed several issues. She discussed the recent shootings in Boston, Chicago, and Jacksonville, emphasizing that white supremacy has no place in America. She also mentioned President Biden's upcoming trip to Hanoi, Vietnam, where he will meet with key leaders to discuss deepening cooperation between the United States and Vietnam. Additionally, she mentioned the President's participation in the G20 Summit in New Delhi and his upcoming commemoration of the 22nd anniversary of the September 11th terror attacks. Jean-Pierre also addressed questions about education, gun violence, the possibility of a government shutdown, and the President's age. She emphasized the administration's commitment to education and supporting schools, as well as the President's focus on unity and bipartisanship.